parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various warning lights to appear on the dashboard, including the ABS, airbag, start/stop, and seatbelt lights, which can lead to confusion, distraction, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Random appearance of warning lights on the dashboard
including seatbelt
parking brake
and airbag lights
even when there is no apparent issue; sudden shutdown of the vehicle while driving; inability to restart the vehicle; and malfunctioning of the start/stop function.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Coolant System Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the engine and malfunctioning of the coolant system can cause the vehicle to shut down suddenly, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Engine stalling while driving; sudden appearance of the engine coolant hot indicator light; steering wheel locking; and inability to restart the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Oil Consumption and Engine Performance Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption and engine performance issues can lead to engine failure, causing a loss of power and control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Excessive oil consumption; engine shuddering; inability to accelerate; and malfunctioning of the vehicle collision warning system.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Headlight and Front Lighting System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of multiple front lights, including headlights, daytime running lights, marker lights, and signal lights, can significantly reduce visibility and increase the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Multiple front lights fail simultaneously
including headlights
daytime running lights
marker lights
and signal lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The 2-4 second delay in acceleration from a complete stop can increase the risk of accidents, especially when merging into traffic or crossing intersections.
symptoms: A noticeable delay in acceleration when starting from a complete stop
making it difficult to merge into traffic or respond to changing road conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unexplained Vehicle Shutdown and Loud Bang
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shutdown of the vehicle while in motion can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if it occurs on a highway or at high speeds. The loud bang noise can be unsettling and may indicate a more serious underlying issue.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts down unexpectedly while in motion
sometimes accompanied by a loud bang noise
which can be felt through the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the forward collision system module can cause the system to malfunction, leading to a lack of warning or intervention in potential collision scenarios, which can increase the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The forward collision warning system fails to operate
the system displays an error message
the system does not provide warnings or alerts in potential collision scenarios.
